          <p>The figure shows the structure of a transferase, 2WNS chain A. The top structure shows a prediction where default cut-off has been used (NetTurnP) and the bottom structure shows the same structure where cut-off tweak has been applied (NetTurnP-tweak). Assigned β-turns are yellow, false positives are red, and the residues in green are where assignments and predictions agree. Figures were made using the PYMOL software <xref rid="pone.0015079-DeLano1" ref-type="bibr">[44]</xref>.</p>
